This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) category as it deals with video representation learning and action recognition. It also involves the use of human masks, which is a common technique in computer vision. Additionally, the use of adversarial loss and confusion loss suggests that the paper may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) categories. The paper may also be relevant to Multimedia (cs.MM) and Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) categories as it involves analyzing videos and scenes.
